      },
      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:7:3:63:45",
      "relations": null,
      "text": [
        " لَا يُخَلَّدُ فِي السِّجْنِ إِلَّا ثَلَاثَةٌ الَّذِي يُمَثِّلُ وَ الْمَرْأَةُ تَرْتَدُّ عَنِ الْإِسْلَامِ وَ السَّارِقُ بَعْدَ قَطْعِ الْيَدِ وَ الرِّجْلِ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Ali Bin Ibrahim, from his father, from one of his companions, from Hammad, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> having said: ‘No one is to be imprisoned for ever except for three – One who severely tortures someone, and the woman who reneges from Al-Islam, and the thief (who steals) after the cutting of the hand and the leg’."
        ]
      }
    }
